    double m_wage {};
};Related contentWe discuss why member variables of a class are often prefixed with an “m_” in upcoming lesson14.5 -- Public and private members and access specifiersTo demonstrate how similar classes and structs can be, the following program is equivalent to the one we presented at the top of the lesson, butDateis now a class instead of a struct:#include <iostream>

